commandParameter.commandParameterDescription:
Specifies a buffer or inverter to delete. If you specify an inverter, the command finds another inverter on the net and deletes the back-to-back pair in order to preserve the logical equivalence. Instances are deleted only if they are tied to	each other.
					To specify a pair of instances, enclose the instances in braces.
					-inst { inst1 inst2 }
